<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 10 June Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] The NEW YORK TIMES recently reported that Japan is 
taking a negative attitude toward UN economic sanctions against 
the DPRK (North Korea) over its alleged nuclear weapons 
development. 
  Commenting on this, a top Foreign Ministry official stated 
on 
9 June that, the report "does not correctly describe the stance 
of the Japanese Government." He stressed the Japanese 
Government is positively taking part in all international 
negotiations to persuade North Korea to accept inspections by 
the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), including 
trilateral talks with the ROK and the United States. 

