BFN 

  [Text] At a House of Representatives' Budget Committee 
meeting on 8 June, Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata commented on the 
DPRK's suspected development of nuclear weapons. He said: "The 
situation will become serious if nuclear arms development should 
progress. In some cases, sanctions will be necessary to deal 
with such a situation. In a conflict of power, I think 
(imposing sanctions) is effective under certain circumstances." 
In this way, the prime minister stressed the effectiveness of 
sanctions by the UN Security Council. 

