BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 10 June Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] On 9 June, a top Foreign Ministry official showed a 
prudent stance toward a Russian proposal for an early 
international conference among the United States, Russia, China, 
Japan, the ROK, and the DPRK (North Korea), on North Korea's 
alleged nuclear weapons development. He said: "I believe 
neither the United States nor the ROK fully supports the idea 
right now." 
  However, the official noted the idea may become worthy of 
consideration when the UN Security Council [UNSC] adopts a 
resolution on the issue, saying: "It appears some nations would 
support an international conference following the UNSC 
resolution." 

</TEXT>

