<H3> <TI>   LDP Leader Hints Dropping No-Confidence Motion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    LDP Leader Hints Dropping No-Confidence Motion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1006124594 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 10 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 1 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1006124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the late hours of 9 June, a top official of the 
Liberal Democratic Party [LDP] commented on the possibility of 
his party dropping its plan to submit a no-confidence motion 
against the administration of Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata. He 
said: "That possibility cannot be ruled out." 
  A top official of the Social Democratic Party of Japan 
recently announced that it would not align itself with the LDP 
regarding an LDP-proposed no-confidence motion. The top LDP 
official was hinting at the possibility the LDP may scrap its 
plan to submit the no- confidence motion in light of such 
circumstances. 

</TEXT>

