<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   List of Delegates to 15 Jun Roundtable Revealed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    List of Delegates to 15 Jun Roundtable Revealed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1206102794 Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA in Cambodian 12 
Jun 94 pp 1, 2 </F>

<F P=103> BK1206102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh REAKSMEI KAMPUCHEA </F>
<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] A government official revealed that the Royal 
Government of Cambodia [RGC] and the Khmer Rouge have already 
chosen their representatives to the roundtable commission. The 
four representatives from the RGC are: "Sok An, Tol Loah, Yu 
Hokkri, and Chhuo Leanghuot." But this official did not confirm 
whether there will be any change in this composition before the 
commission's scheduled meeting is held in Phnom Penh on 15 June 
under the chairmanship of Samdech Chakkrei Nhoek Chulong. The 
roundtable commission delegation from the Party of Democratic 
Kampuchea [PDK] will arrive in Phnom Penh on 13 June to attend 
the meeting. 
  According to a report on 10 June by the CAMBODIAN DAILY in 
English, the four PDK delegates on the commission will be chosen 
from among the following six officials: "Chan Youran, Mak Ben, 
Tep Khunnal, Tup Kiem, Meas Chey, and Sok Roeu." 
  The topics on the agenda are: 
  1) The answer from both sides on whether they will or will 
not accept a permanent cease-fire in Cambodia. 
  2) The PDK's proposal on the minimal policy program. 
  Various analysts have expressed doubts that the 15 June 
meeting will be successful because the Pyongyang roundtable 
failed despite the fact that it was chaired by the king himself. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

