<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Czech Republic, Slovakia, Germany Create Jobs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech Republic, Slovakia, Germany Create Jobs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0906090394 Hanoi VNA in English 0634 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0906090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 9 -- With financial assistance from 
the former Czechoslovak government's job creation programme, the 
Ministry of Labour, War Invalids and Social Affairs has approved 
219 projects with a total loan capital of VND 25.9 billion to 
provide 10,120 people with jobs. 
  The programme includes jobs for 2,628 guest workers 
returning from Czech and Slovakia. 
  The labour ministry has passed 31 free-of-charge job 
training projects for 1,594 workers returning from Czech and 
Slovakia with total funds of more than VND 4.1 billion. Many 
job-training courses were held in 23 provinces and cities. 
  In 1994 around 500 more projects will be implemented. They 
have loan capital of about vnd 60 billion to create jobs for 
12,000 people, 5,000 of them former workers from Czech and 
Slovakia. 
  - Germany has funded nearly VND 3.96 billion to 28 projects 
of Vietnamese guest workers returning from Germany in Vinh Phu 
Province to help them set up their businesses or participate in 
other businesses. Thanks to self-generated income and loan 
capital 28 private businesses were set up or expanded their 
production and business, providing nearly 650 people with jobs. 

</TEXT>

