<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    North's Decision on IAEA Withdrawal Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1306151394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 1500 GMT 13 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1306151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP report from Tokyo] </F>
  [Text] Quoting a North Korean source, Japan's JIJI News 
Agency reported that North Korea decided to withdraw from the 
International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA]. 
  JIJI News Agency reported that through its Central News 
Agency, North Korea issued a statement by the spokesman of the 
North Korean Foreign Ministry on the evening of 13 June and said 
that North Korea decided to withdraw from the IAEA. JIJI News 
Agency also reported that in the statement North Korea 
emphasized that if international sanctions are carried out 
regarding suspicions of its nuclear development, it means an 
immediate war, and that the war will be merciless [mujabihangot]. 

</TEXT>

