<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It was confirmed that even after the International 
Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] adopted a resolution to take 
sanctions against North Korea, two IAEA inspectors still remain 
in North Korea and are carrying out inspection activities of the 
work replacing the fuel rods in Yongbyon. 
  Mr. Kyd, IAEA director of public relations [title as heard], 
said that the inspectors are watching over the work to replace 
the fuel rods and are continuing to carry out normal work of 
installing cameras to determine if nuclear materials have been 
diverted. He said that North Korea has not yet taken any 
measures regarding the two inspectors. 

