<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seoul, China Plan Exchange of Public Servants </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seoul, China Plan Exchange of Public Servants </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0906031894 Seoul YONHAP in English 0223 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0906031894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 9 (YONHAP) -- An exchange of public 
servants between South Korea and China will be realized from 
June 28 for the first time in history, the Government 
Administration Ministry said Thursday. 
  The government plans to send 16 grade-five, working-level 
officials to a three-week group training course for public 
servants offered by the Chinese personnel ministry from June 28 
to July 19. 
  The exchange is based on an agreement to expand personnel 
cooperation signed by Seoul and Beijing last March. 
  China will also send about 15 public servants to South Korea 
in early September to attend the central officials training 
institute here, a Ministry official said. 
  The exchange of public officials is designed to promote 
friendly and cooperative relations between the two nations' 
civil servants by widening their knowledge of the other 
country's reform policy. 

</TEXT>

