<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   IAEA Inspector Leaves DPRK, Arrives in PRC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IAEA Inspector Leaves DPRK, Arrives in PRC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106094994 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0900 GMT 11 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1106094994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Beijing-based correspondent Yi Tong-sik] </F>
  [Text] A member of the inspection team of the International 
Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA], who remained in North Korea and 
observed the process of the replacement of the fuel rods of the 
nuclear reactor in Yongbyon, arrived in Beijing today. The 
member of the inspection team, who is confirmed to be (Vladimir 
Luklo), came to Beijing aboard a North Korean Koryo airliner 
this morning, with baggage which looked like verification 
documents, without carrying inspection equipment. 
  The inspection team member (Luklo), arriving at the Beijing 
airport, refused to reply to the questions on the progress of 
the fuel rod replacement of the nuclear reactor in Yongbyon, 
asking the reporters to confirm it through the IAEA 
headquarters. He added that he would return to Vienna as soon 
as possible. 
  The inspection team member went to North Korea with 
Heinonen, 
chief of the inspection section, on 17 May, and remained in 
North Korea after Section Chief Heinonen returned to the IAEA 
headquarters with Inspection Department Director Perricos on 28 
May and observed the process of the fuel rod replacement of the 
nuclear reactor in Yongbyon. 

</TEXT>

