<H3> <TI>   Mobilization Exercise Planned in Focus Lens-94 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mobilization Exercise Planned in Focus Lens-94 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1306022994 Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN in Korean 13 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK1306022994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Kim Chong-tu] </F>
  [Text] It was learned on 12 June that the ROK Government 
plans to conduct the ROK-U.S. joint "Ulchi-Focus Lens-94 
exercise" on a large scale for 14 days, from 22 August to 4 
September, to inspect the nation's readiness for mobilization. 
  To inspect the nation's capabilities to mobilize resources 
and recover damages, during the 22-27 Ulchi exercise, the 
government plans to select Seoul as an exhibition city in 
conducting exercises for preparing against disasters, 
stabilizing the people's livelihoods, and maintaining the 
government's functions. 
  According to authorities concerned, government ministries 
will conduct surprise exercises of their own, as well. For 
example, the Ministries of Home Affairs and Transportation will 
conduct an exercise for mobilizing personnel and vehicles; the 
Ministry of Agriculture, Forest, and Fisheries will conduct a 
river-crossing exercise for barges loaded with grain and an 
exercise for distributing grain; the Ministry of Health and 
Social Affairs will conduct an exercise for guarding against 
poisonous gas; and the Ministries of Home Affairs and Trade, 
Industry, and Energy will conduct an exercise for preparing 
against the rupture of electricity, water, and gas supplies. 

</TEXT>

