<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seoul Decides on Cultural, Sports Attaches </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seoul Decides on Cultural, Sports Attaches </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0906141794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0933 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0906141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 9 (YONHAP) -- The government has decided 
to send cultural and sports attaches to six cities in five 
foreign countries. "With President Kim Yong-sam's approval on 
last May 23, we have since early this month been consulting with 
the Foreign Ministry and other related offices on the dispatch 
of cultural and sports attaches," Culture and Sports Minister Yi 
Min-sop told reporters on Thursday. He said a cultural and 
sports attache will be posted to each of New York, Los Angeles, 
Paris, Tokyo, Moscow and Beijing. 
  The attaches will be selected from among those officials 
armed with specialized knowledge and good foreign language 
proficiency in the areas of culture and sports, Yi said. The 
duties of the cultural and sports attaches will be to excavate, 
restore or study Korea's historical relics abroad, support 
overseas cultural, art, sports and youth programs, and assist in 
the protection and exports of Korea's cultural pieces. 

</TEXT>

