<H4>    SDPJ Legislators Leave for Pyongyang </H4>

<F P=102> OW1006042594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0353 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1006042594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 10 KYODO -- A delegation of legislators 
from the Social Democratic Party (SDP) left Japan on Friday [10 
June] to visit north korea via Beijing. 
  The legislators will arrive in Pyongyang on Saturday. They 
will hold talks with senior officials of the Korean Workers' 
Party on North Korea's nuclear issue before returning to Tokyo 
next Tuesday, SDP officials said. 
  The SDP is Japan's second largest party after the Liberal 
Democratic Party, both in the opposition camp. 

</TEXT>

