<H3> <TI>   Telecommunications Talks With PRC Set for 15 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Telecommunications Talks With PRC Set for 15 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1306104394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0927 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1306104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 13 KYODO -- Japan and China will hold 
talks Wednesday [15 June] on the telecommunications and postal 
service fields, officials at Japan's Posts and 
Telecommunications Ministry said Monday. 
  They said representatives from both countries' posts and 
telecommunications ministries will discuss schedules for setting 
up a proposed forum for bilateral cooperation. 
  The forum is expected to become a stage whereby government 
and private-sector representatives from both countries can 
exchange opinions and information. 
  Representatives will also discuss plans by Japanese firms to 
help upgrade the information infrastructure in Nanjing and 
Shanghai through research and development projects, the 
officials added. 

</TEXT>

