<H3> <TI>   Komeito Leader Urges SDPJ To Return to Ruling Fold </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Komeito Leader Urges SDPJ To Return to Ruling Fold </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1106034094 Tokyo KYODO in English 0316 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1106034094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 11 KYODO -- Yuichi Ichikawa, secretary 
general of the Soka Gakkai-backed Komeito, called on the Social 
Democratic Party (SDP) [SDPJ -- of Social Democratic Party of 
Japan] Saturday [11 June] to return to the ruling coalition to 
help stabilize Japanese politics. 
  In a speech to senior officials of Komeito's prefectural 
chapters from across the country, Ichikawa rejected calls within 
the SDP for prime minister Tsutomu Hata's cabinet to voluntarily 
quit. 
  But Ichikawa praised the second largest opposition party for 
exploring the possibility of its returning to the coalition, 
which it bolted in April over the abrupt formation of "Kaishin 
(Innovation)" by other coalition partners, including Hata's 
Shinseito, Komeito and the Democratic Socialist Party. 
  The Komeito official criticized the Liberal Democratic Party 
for hinting at introducing a no-confidence motion against the 
Hata administration and cautioned the SDP against going along 
with the LDP on the matter. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

