<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Comments Concerning Economic Recovery </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Comments Concerning Economic Recovery </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    EPA: BOJ Survey Reflects Steady Recovery </H4>

<F P=102> OW1006084894 Tokyo KYODO in English 0811 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1006084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 10 KYODO -- Vice Minister Tsutomu 
Tanaka of the Economic Planning Agency [EPA] said Friday [10 
June] the Bank of Japan's [BOJ] quarterly economic survey 
released earlier in the day reflected steady progress toward 
recovery of the domestic economy. 
  Tanaka told a news conference the survey, known as Tankan, 
was a "big plus factor" for the domestic economy and the agency 
hopes the government's stimulus measures will lead to 
full-fledged recovery. 
  He cited sluggish capital investment plans by medium and 
small enterprises as a minus factor which can be traced to 
growing investment overseas by manufacturers. 
  Tanaka said the central bank report was one of the factors 
for judging domestic economic trends and that the agency will 
take all such factors into account in making its own assessment 
of the economy. 

</TEXT>

