<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK, U.S. Actions Denounced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK, U.S. Actions Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1306101494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1005 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1306101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["`Sanctions' Racket of Doomed Puppet Clique" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 13 (KCNA) -- The traitor Kim 
Yong-sam in "a telephone dialogue" with U.S. President Bill 
Clinton on June 10 cried that "sanctions against the North must 
be promoted continuously" and, on the previous day, in "a 
telephone dialogue" with Japanese Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata, 
he said "U.N. sanctions against the North are inevitable," a 
Seoul-based radio report said. 
  On June 11, puppet Unification Minister Yi Hong-ku and 
puppet 
Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu met U.S. State Undersecretary 
Tarnoff in Seoul and prattled that U.N. Security Council's 
sanctions against the North are inevitable". 
  This tongue-wagging of the South Korean puppet clique is a 
never-to-be condoned criminal act to leave fellow countrymen 
victims of outside forces by realizing "sanctions against North" 
through the United Nations" by all means by entreating the U.S. 
and Japanese masters. 
  We solemnly warned the Kim Yong-sam group that "sanctions" 
against our Republic is immediately a war and a war is merciless. 
  This notwithstanding, the Kim Yong-sam traitor clique are 
making desperate efforts to get "sanctions" taken against the 
North with the help of foreign forces. This is a dangerous 
criminal act which may bring an unpredictable grave situation to 
the Korean peninsula. 
  The outcries of the Kim Yong-sam group over "sanctions" will 
precipitate their own destruction. 
  The South Korean puppet clique must act with discretion, 
clearly mindful of the tragic end. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

