<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reacts to U.S. Resolution on Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Reacts to U.S. Resolution on Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1206082594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0809 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1206082594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["United States Must Clearly Know the Will of the Korean </F>
People" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- The U.S. House of 
Representatives reportedly passed on Thursday a "resolution" 
urging "sanctions" against the DPRK. 
  This is entirely unreasonable. This is a wanton violation of 
the sovereignty and dignity of our Republic and an unpardonable 
strong-arm act to stifle our socialism. 
  The U.S. House of Representatives also carried a 
"resolution" 
urging the readjustment of the schedule of the "Team Spirit" 
joint military manoeuvres this year and "strengthening of the 
combat power" of the South Korean puppet army. This revealed 
again the sinister intention of the United States to contain the 
DPRK by force of arms. 
  This can be easily judged from the facts that Robert 
Gallucci, U.S. assistant secretary of state, blared that "the 
United States does not rule out military sanctions against North 
Korea" in a hearing at the subcommittee of Asian and Pacific 
affairs of the U.S. House of Representatives on the 9th of June 
and Hamilton, chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of the 
U.S. House of Representatives, next day said the U.S. had no 
other option but to fight and that it was necessary to increase 
the potentials of the U.S. troops in South Korea and the puppet 
armed forces. 
  If the United States chooses a reckless adventure, ignoring 
our repeated warnings, we will take a decisive self-defensive 
measure. 
  The United States must clearly see our unshakable will and 
resolution and immediately stop the adventurous war provocation 
moves. 

</TEXT>

