<H3> <TI>   U.S. Decried for Not Upholding Joint Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Decried for Not Upholding Joint Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106232794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2115 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1106232794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2115 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] One year has passed since our country and the United 
States announced their joint statement confirming the 
prohibition of using armed forces -- including nuclear weapons 
-- or posing a threat by them; the mutual respect for their 
sovereignty; and the nonintervention into each other's internal 
affairs. 
  Over this period, the United States has not kept, even a 
little, the principles of the joint statement. Instead, it has 
been the subject of ridicule and denouncement by the people 
throughout the world because of their intentional aggravation of 
tensions on the Korean peninsula. 
  Up to date since the DPRK-U.S. joint statement was issued, 
approximately 150 countries throughout the world and a great 
many international and regional organizations have held rallies 
and demonstrations to urge the United States to sincerely 
implement the principles agreed upon by the two sides of the 
DPRK and the United States. Also, they have severely denounced 
the treacherous act of the United States by releasing 
statements, press statements, and articles. 

</TEXT>

