<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Denies Yemeni Arms Contract Report </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Denies Yemeni Arms Contract Report </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106110994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1056 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["DPRK FM Spokesman Refutes Reports About 'Arms Deal </F>
Contract' With Southern Yemen" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 11 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
Foreign Ministry of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea 
today answered a question put by KCNA on the reports about an 
"arms deal contract" allegedly signed by the DPRK with the 
Southern Yemen forces. 
  He said: 
  Some foreign news media are now spreading reports that the 
DPRK signed an "arms deal a "new contract" with the Southern 
Yemen forces, according to which it will supply Aden with jet 
planes, tanks, tactical missiles and other combat equipment. 
  This is an utterly groundless fabrication. 
  It is by no means accidental that such reports are afloat 
when the manoeuvres to stifle the DPRK over the fictitious 
"nuclear issue" have reached a grave stage. 
  We cannot but think that they are underlain by the political 
intention to impair the authority of the DPRK and isolate it in 
the international arena. 
  Our country which has steadfastly maintained the principle 
of 
non-interference in relations with other countries consistently 
calls for a negotiated solution of disputes between the parties 
concerned. 
  The dispute between the Northern and Southern Yemen is 
merely 
an internal dispute, and it is inconceivable for us to "help" 
any one side. 
  From the very moment the dispute broke out between the North 
and the South of Yemen we have hoped to see it solved peacefully 
at an early date in the interests of the entire Yemeni people 
without outside interference, and there is no change in this 
principled stand of ours now. 
  Truth will be made clear. 
  No insidious attempt can tarnish the image of our dignified 
Republic or damage the excellent relations between our country 
and Yemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

