<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Sends Greetings to Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Sends Greetings to Yeltsin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106111694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1051 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 11 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il-song 
of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea today sent a 
message of greetings to Boris Nikolayevich Yeltsin, president of 
the Russian Federation, on the national day of Russia. 
  President Kim Il-song in his message expressed the belief 
that the relations between the two peoples will develop on the 
principle of independence, equality and non-interference in 
other's internal affairs. 

</TEXT>

