<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister on Cambodian Aid, U.S. Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister on Cambodian Aid, U.S. Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1106105494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 11 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1106105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vietnam was adjusting its foreign policy in order to 
serve the country's top priorities to meet its economic 
development. This was said by Deputy Foreign Minister Le Mai in 
an international investment seminar in Hanoi. 
  He said: Vietnam has no time for getting involve in 
hostilities in neighboring Cambodia. On military aid to 
Cambodia, Mr. Le Mai said: It was no longer Vietnam's duty to 
do that. Vietnam did once and that was enough. Now it's turn 
for other countries if they want to help the Cambodian 
Government fight against the Khmer Rouge. 
  Mr. Le Mai also said the United States will soon open a 
diplomatic mission in Vietnam and that the only remaining 
obstacle was the difficulty in finding suitable accommodation in 
Hanoi. He said economic development was a top priority for 
Vietnam. 

</TEXT>

