<H4>    Hata Sends Verbal Message to DPRK </H4>

<F P=102> OW1106123394 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 11 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 7 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1106123394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Taku Yamasaki, former director general of the 
Defense Agency, and Yoichi Tani, former director general of the 
Hokkaido and Okinawa Development Agency, both legislators 
affiliated with the opposition Liberal Democratic Party [LDP], 
will visit North Korea on 14 June. Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata 
met them on 10 June to discuss the issue of North Korea's 
suspected development of nuclear weapons. During the meeting, 
the prime minister told them, "I hope both of you will make 
North Korea understand that the international community is 
paying great attention to the North Korean nuclear issue and is 
deeply concerned over the issue." The prime minister also said, 
"I hope your forthcoming visit to North Korea will serve to help 
it open its door to and promote a candid dialogue with other 
nations," adding that he hoped they would convey that remark to 
North Korea as his verbal message to that country. 

</TEXT>

